Rating: 2
The caramel filling is exactly what I was seeking to use in my caramel apple macarons (with the addition of apple flavoring oil). The recipe here for chocolate macarons (or "macarOOns" -- shudder) is atrocious. I can't believe the instructions actually tell you your cookies should be cracked! These are "macawrongs", not macarons. Macarons should have a smooth dome and a lovely, bubbly foot. Don't trust a macaron recipe with volume measurements instead of weight. You have to let the piped shells sit out until no longer sticky to the touch before you bake them. Chocolate macarons are tricky; you need to let the batter sit covered airtight for a few hours before piping them.

