Rating: 4
I've had the most success with this macaron recipe vs. those from tartelette, i love macarons, David Lebovitz, etc. Yes, the photo should be updated (should not have cracked cookies for true French macarons). I usually make 1/2 recipe with 3 L egg whites, scant 2 c. powdered sugar, 3/4 c. Just Almond Meal from Trader Joe's, 3 T unsweetened cocoa powder -- latter 3 ingredients combined in a food processor. I only pipe one baking sheet at a time, let it develop a skin/crust before baking (last night, this took 30 min.), and baked 8-9 min. in 400F oven. With 1/2 caramel recipe this yields ~2 dozen small sandwiches. They are truly delicious -- nice combo of crunch, chew, melt-in-your-mouth sweetness. And my cookies developed a "foot," one of the measures of success in the macaron world. Love it!

