Rating: 3
The macarons in this recipe come out cracked. If you have macarons in France, they are never cracked. They are smooth and have a "foot" or a separation from the bottom of the cookie to the top. (Many people here thought that was a mistake). I tried to get my cookies to come out without cracks and with that smooth, authentic look, but it seemed impossible. I cooked the cookies for 7 -8 minutes, the 11 minutes was too long in my oven. The cookies taste good, but don't look like a real French macaron. The carmel sauce was nearly impossible to make following this recipe. Not enough liquid, I ended up with crystallized sugar. I had to add a great deal more water to make it work.

