Rating: 3
Exactly what you are looking for if you want the Macaroons you would find in the bakeries in Europe. The fillings wer very easy...recipe is very straight forward, but I would suggest taking them out of the fridge and let them sit for a few before you try to fill the cookies, or else it will be quite difficult (if not IMPOSSIBLE with the caramel). The cookies themselves were SUPER difficult to make for me, because I didnt have the right kind of food processor (just a little chopper--tiny kitchen, have to make certain sacrifices), but after about 4 hours of work, the end product was fine. To make the process a bit quicker, I tried piping the dough (VERY sticky, by the way) onto parchment paper and then sliding that onto the baking sheet once they cooled and putting it into the oven. I think that was a bad idea, as it might have given the dough too much time to set, because none of those came out correctly. I would suggest putting the dough into the oven immediately after piping it out. If you do, you should get perfectly shaped (and delicious) cookies. Watch them like a hawk however, because they can burn easily, and you may have to turn down the heat a smidge (but not too much).

